sal and intransitive verbs). The syntactic analyses focus on positional arrangements of aspectual and verbal units (V2, Verb Raising). The data are mainly drawn from English; perspectives on other Germanic languages are included.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 01. Dez 2022) 0aGenerative grammar. 0aGrammar, Comparative and generalxGrammatical categories. 0aGrammar, Comparative and generalxVerbals. 0aLexicology. 7aLANGUAGE ARTS & DISCIPLINES / Linguistics / General.2bisacsh1 aBode, Stefanie, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDehé, Nicole, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFarke, Hildegard, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFelser, Claudia, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJanßen, Hero, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJanßen, Hero, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aKaiser, Alexander, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKrivokapic, Jelena, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRauh, Gisa, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aTappe, Hans Thilo, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aTuschinsky, Joachim, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWanner, Anja, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Backlist Complete English Language 2000-2014 PART1z978311023857008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Backlist Linguistics and Semiotics  2000-2014 (EN)z978311023845708iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Linguistics and Semiotics 2000 - 2014z97831106369